    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breed of dog that originated in China, and was introduced to England by Dutch traders at the end of the 17th century. The pug has a short muzzle, a black mask on the face, tightly curled tail, large head with prominent, dark eyes, and small, drooping ears. At maturity, it stands 10 to 11 inches (25.5 to 28 cm) and weighs about 14 to 18 pounds (6 to 8 kg). Its coat is short and glossy with the color ranging from apricot or silver fawn to black. In art, the pug can be found alongside sitters in portrait paintings, and as porcelain objects.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
